<br>
It just seems that something *always* happens, and both tanks drop and i generally get elected to start tanking.  /shrug.<br>
<br>
Generally this against those little speedy gonzales wyverns and it seems like our warrior drops just about the time the damn thing finally gets slowed.<br>
<br>
I agree with the spells... the only stuns i load are for positioning.  (quellious thingamajig and force) I usually will try to blast off both of them when one of the white wurms start to either (a) CH or (b) gate.  Sometimes it works, sometimes it doesn't, but i like to feel like i tried.<br>
<br>
I load Celest heal, Sheal, and Prexus wave of healing, i try to unload my cleric as much as possible so they can concentrate on someone actually tanking vs our group.<br>
<br>
When the mobs enrage, i leave attack on until i get a riposte message, at which point, i turn off attack, move a bit, and then try again.  If i get hit with another riposte, i'll turn off attack until the mob is un enraged, and just /assist heal.<br>
<br>
My guild is not in NToV yet, so all my experiance is based on doing HoT.<br>
<br>
regards,<br>
