<br>
Resist gear:<br>
head- Frog Crown<br>
Ring- Velium Diamond wedding rings<br>
Neck- BD item<br>
Wrist- BD item<br>
Whatever else - good<br>
Circle of Seasons is your big friend<br>
<br>
I regularly use Word and force spells not for the Stun<br>
but for the knockback to position mobs. Take care - <br>
you have to be smart so you do not take aggro.<br>
<br>
Know your tanks and MA. While that 55 warrior may <br>
have defensive - his taunt key is effectively broken <br>
until 60.<br>
<br>
Use the walls to keep from taking AoE damage until<br>
you are called in to melee. Stupid to take extra damage.<br>
<br>
2h weapons that do good damage and control your aggro <br>
are just the ticket.<br>
<br>
White and blues can gate and heal - use all your palie skills to <br>
keep them from it.<br>
<br>
If aggroed - go TO the MA and stop attack - even DA if needed - do not want the MOB following you around.<br>
&lt;so keep DA memmed&gt;<br>
<br>
Have /target MA hotkeyed so you can check main tank<br>
Ancient Shard Wyrvens and Veiment&lt;sp?&gt; Wyrven do incredible damage quickly - the clerics may be slow or<br>
the Warrior slow in disc. LOH might save a wipeout<br>
<br>
Have fun<br>
